name: molly conger
tweet: a heavy consent agenda tonight, with item 10 being kind of a Big Deal around here  https://t.co/Y9L4mbeMHG

name: molly conger
tweet: members of the 2016 blue ribbon commission issued this statement yesterday, urging council to take appropriate action on the statues immediately  https://t.co/QhsV4txlOw

name: molly conger
tweet: there is some public comment on the consent agenda. former city councilor kristin szakos says the recent state supreme court decision allows council to remove the statues immediately, but she respects their decision to follow the process outlined by the state law.

name: molly conger
tweet: "our moral toxic waste cannot be exported to do its damage elsewhere," szakos says. we can't just MOVE these statues to be displayed elsewhere. the SCOVA decision reversed the attorneys fees awarded to the monument fund - the city should use that money to remove the statues ASAP.

name: molly conger
tweet: szakos says "speed is of the essence," and urges council to vote to remove the statues immediately following the public hearing they are about to set for next month. "i urge you to remove them, whether or not their final disposition has been determined."

name: molly conger
tweet: "this is really a scar," hawkins says of charlottesville's confederate statues. "an abatement has to occur." "they're an errant framing of history, one that i have to teach against."

name: molly conger
tweet: next is UVA professor larycia hawkins, also about the statues. she traces her own lineage to people held in slavery here in virginia. "this place is pocked with memories and histories," she says. these statues are, to her, "akin to superfund sites."

name: molly conger
tweet: cali gaston says these statues do great damage to the community by occupying public space with the message that not all people count. "it's not good for charlottesville on any level," she says, speaking as a downtown business owner.

name: molly conger
tweet: "they are more than just symbols - we've seen that they serve as motivations for hate," gathers says of the confederate statues that continue to serve as lightning rods for hate. even 3.5 years after they sparked a nazi rally, they still draw hate group members to them.

name: molly conger
tweet: don gathers, a co-signer on the statement from the blue ribbon commission, says the BRC did their jobs & now it's time for council to do theirs - the statues need to be removed and until they can be removed, they need to be covered.

name: molly conger
tweet: lena seville has also called in to stress that just moving the statues out of *our* town square isn't enough - we need to ensure they aren't just moved to some other  public square where they'll do the same harm.  she suggests melting them down & transforming them.

name: molly conger
tweet: adrienne dent reiterates the same talking points as previous callers: -get rid of them now -don't just put them in some other public place -maybe just melt the lee statue

name: molly conger
tweet: ok that concludes the public comment on the consent agenda. nothing from council in response to what was shared by the community. mayor walker asks if item 8 can be pulled for a separate vote.  https://t.co/5lAqyt3RnB

name: molly conger
tweet: city manager chip boyles says council can hold the public hearing about the statue removal at their june 7 meeting and the statues can be removed 30 days after that hearing.

name: molly conger
tweet: the consent agenda, minus item 8 (a budget amendment for CDBG allocations) passes unanimously. item 8 passes 4-1 with mayor walker dissenting.

name: molly conger
tweet: boyles says they still do not have the full guidance from the us treasury on the rules and regulations governing how they can spend the american rescue plan $. the first payment comes in less than 2 weeks, so those rules should be coming soon.

name: molly conger
tweet: boyles says 64 people applied for the position of executive director of the police civilian review board. the posting has closed, so they'll be making a hire from that pool.

name: molly conger
tweet: on to public comment. leonard schoppa has concerns that the draft land use plan is asking some neighborhoods to take on the burden of increased density. it sounds like he supports density... just not in certain neighborhoods, such as his.

name: molly conger
tweet: maddy green from the charlottesville low income housing coalition says modest solutions like adding ADUs aren't enough - there needs to be mandatory inclusive zoning & upzoning of previously exclusive neighborhoods.

name: molly conger
tweet: jennifer koch is a consultant on the cville plans together project working on the land use map.  there are some community engagement sessions coming up - you can see those & register to attend on the website   https://t.co/iLC0uIJvy2

name: molly conger
tweet: stacy miller has concerns about the proposed 21 unit development 915 6th st (on the agenda tonight for a critical slope waiver). she makes a vague allusion to concerns about affordable housing, but doesn't elaborate on them.

name: molly conger
tweet: kate fraleigh, speaking for the people's coalition, urges council to pass a new ordinance for the police civilian review board with all the powers authorized by recent state legislation including the ability to perform independent investigations & subpoena power

name: molly conger
tweet: peter krebs thanks council for the proclamation about bike month & says the piedmont environmental council has an event later this week called 'cycling for sustainable cities'  https://t.co/jdwlrChqiV

name: molly conger
tweet: ms rosia says she wants to talk to council about the 'gang violence,' referring to the shocking number of shots fired incidents this year. she says she is 'a former gang leader' herself in her youth and warns that more violence is coming.

name: molly conger
tweet: on the subject of the shootings, mayor walker says one thing that goes unaddressed in these conversations is "what IS here for our youth?" creating opportunities for young people, providing safe & fulfilling extracurriculars can make a big difference.

name: molly conger
tweet: on the subject of land use & affordable housing, councilor michael payne says density is necessary but not sufficient. we need to explore community wealth building strategies, keep pushing for land trusts

name: molly conger
tweet: (having spent the last several years defending the city in a lawsuit based on a decision a previous council made to remove the statues, i can understand why she is choosing the most conservative course of action here but i'm not sure other attorneys would agree this is REQUIRED)

name: molly conger
tweet: city atty lisa robertson says 'while the supreme court decision contained some favorable language,' it was based on the law before it changed in the last GA session. her advice as the city's atty is that the city should follow the procedure laid out by the new law.

name: molly conger
tweet: on the subject of the statues - people have been asking council WHY they are choosing to follow the slower removal process laid out by the state law when the supreme court decision appears to mean we do not have to

name: molly conger
tweet: and we are BACK and we are having a public hearing about issuing $18mil in BONDS  https://t.co/ArdV8hpBPl

name: molly conger
tweet: look, we're not bragging or anything, but the city of charlottesville is one of only 12 localities in the commonwealth with a triple A bond rating, so that's neat right?

name: molly conger
tweet: shockingly, NO ONE wanted to make a public comment about the bond issuance. councilor snook has a question about interest rates. krisy hammill says they expect a rate of about 1.75%.  the bond issuance carries 5-0.

name: molly conger
tweet: no takers for comment during the public hearing on the community development block grant annual action plan, either. it passes unanimously with just one question from sena magill about organizational capacity, which was answered satisfactorily by erin atak, the grants coordinator

name: molly conger
tweet: now an SUP for 64 university way. during the planning commission hearing, the property owners with concerns about the project all expressed concerns that amounted to "i don't like living near students."  (note that it's surrounded by frat houses & a massive dorm complex)  https://t.co/Rs9hM7607L

name: molly conger
tweet: that seems like a really silly oversight & a simple fix! students who live .5 miles from the university & use the university bus to get around do not all need a parking space or a car at all & the code shouldn't require us to pretend they do.

name: molly conger
tweet: this definitely can't get changed tonight, but one thing that came up in the PC hearing about this SUP is that the city code allows for a reduction in parking requirements if a development is near a CITY bus stop... but no such allowance exists for university transit.

name: molly conger
tweet: ok that issue didn't even come up, perhaps another time. the SUP for 64 university way carried 5-0.   on to the critical slope waiver for 915 6th st SE. staff & the planning commission recommended approval.

name: molly conger
tweet: on to the last agenda item - appointment of the city attorney. council interviewed candidates for the position last week. city manager chip boyles says based on the interviews & his own research, he recommends council appoint current acting city attorney lisa robertson.

name: molly conger
tweet: on the critical slope waiver, mayor walker voted no. vice mayor sena magill asks if she can abstain, then reluctantly votes yes. michael payne votes no, heather & lloyd vote yes.   it carries 3-2.

name: molly conger
tweet: the appointment of acting city attorney lisa robertson as city attorney carries 5-0.  i guess winning a state supreme court appeal is a pretty good audition for the role. glad to see her get the title for the job she's been doing.

name: molly conger
tweet: mayor walker (running for re-election) and heather hill (not running, term up this year) are the current reps to that working group. mayor walker said she would continue as the rep to that working group. no one acknowledged heather's hint that it's an election year.

name: molly conger
tweet: there was an awkward several minute interlude where heather hill tried to explain that the school board wants the councilor on the school reconfiguration working group to be someone currently council who will still be on council next year

name: molly conger
tweet: a motion was made to amend the agenda to add: appropriating $1100 from the council strategic initiatives fund to the juneteeth celebration. it carries 5-0.

name: molly conger
tweet: we're back to matters by the public to close things out. dr larycia hawkins says she moved here not long ago from chicago to teach at UVA & the cost of living here is as high or higher than chicago.

name: molly conger
tweet: "it paints a picture of two charlottesvilles," hawkins says - housing for students was approved "in the blink of an eye," but affordable housing for people outside the university community is such an uphill battle.

name: molly conger
tweet: don gathers says he "wholeheartedly applaud[s] ms robertson's efforts" in the statue case, but he laments the lack of community involvement in the hiring process for the city attorney position.

name: molly conger
tweet: ms rosia, who identifies herself as a victim of the summer of hate, asks council to consider the needs of those victims, urging them to bring the statues down as quickly as possible. (the longer this process drags on, the more likely we are to see more violence because of them)

name: molly conger
tweet: there was a lot of passive aggressive monologuing i didn't feel compelled to capture but the meeting has ended, goodnight.
